N2  - White [1978], in a recent review, has focused attention on the modest and inconsistent findings often evident in earlier job design moderator research. In this paper, we discuss several conceptual and methodological inadequacies that may account for these results and we review evidence supporting the potential value of individual-difference research within the job design field.
